        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-18T18:02:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "actually, this isn\u0027t true anymore: one can create and manipulate qemu{1/2} timers from any thread. Also, I don\u0027t see any reason for it to be virtual.\nThe better interface is to move both vmLock and DeviceOperation parameters to be just constructor arguments and get rid of two-stage initialization completely\n\nIf you can\u0027t make it this way (e.g. because you need it in a LazyInstance\u003c\u003e), just make init() to be non-virtual and to have all these arguments",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 41,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "5555c8f15bcd17a419b3d847f5b2c5f942830bd4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
